The '''Mali firefinch''' ('''''Lagonosticta virata''''') is a species of [[estrildid finch]] found in Western Africa. It has an estimated global extent of occurrence of 120,000&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>. It is found in [[Mali]] and [[Senegal]]. The [[IUCN]] has classified the species as being of [[least concern]]. It is also the mascot of Mali.{{refnec|date=October 2024}}

